The accusations made by the Anti-Mafia Office of Calabria against Mayor Giorgio Dal Torrione and his deputy Rosario Schiavone of the Municipality of Gioia Tauro, who were arrested this morning for involvement in mafia business, are serious.
In handcuffs were also taken Gioacchino Piromalli, the older mediator between the clan and the public administration, and his nephew: the lawyer, who bears the same name as the clan's boss, had already been convicted of involvement in criminal associations of the mafia, at that time to a compensation sum of 10 million euros.
